text: Until there is a big shift in the way horror movies are made it's al, going to be the same crap. JUMP SCARE is not what all horror is about. Horror is my favourite genre but these films are all garbage, go back to the film of the 70's and 80's to see what real horror is. I mean how hard must it be for these horror movie directors, just watch a film like The Shining and follow the same blueprint and you have a REAL horror film. Music, suspense, backstory (optimised through the characters behaviour), fear (it's not all about 2 seconds of jump scare, you need to show the horror for a continues time and make the audience feel the same fear as the character) and so so much more. Jump scare is just lazy filmmaking.

The characters can't even move out because Diana is tied to them. The lights are still useless cause she can turn it off.
